While creating a Selenium project:-
-Create a new Maven project
-Give project name
-JDK 19
-In Archtype type quickstart it will give suggestion select that archtype (It will create a folder structure)
-version 1.4 (Type manually)
-In advance setting you can change your GroiupID that is foldername
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--Previously we have to use 'System.property' to set up the path of drivers
System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver", "/path/to/chromedriver");

If we are using
Chrome then we need to setup the -> Chromedriver
for Edge -> Edgedriver
for Firefox -> Geckodriver
for Safari -> Safaridriver
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--How to run your Selenium first Testcase ?
1. Create a Maven project
2. Install dependencies like
        a.TestNG,
        b.Selenium,
        c.Allure report (testNG)
3. Installed WebBrowsers :
        a. Chrome
        b. Edge
        c. Firefox
        d. Safari
        e. IE browser
        f. Opera
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--Install the webdriver (We need to install webdriver,
            basically we need to to set the path of browser which we are going to use)
    -But nowadays after SELENIUM 4 -> You dont have to setup the driver

Because now we are having 'SELENIUM MANAGER'

the moment we add maven dependency 'SELENIUM MANAGER' downloaded automatically
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Selenium Architecture (Basically based on API)

Search Context (Interface)
WebDriver (Interface)
RemoteWebDriver (Class)
ChromiumDriver (Class)
EdgeDriver (Class)

// Edge driver is copy cloned of Chrome driver
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Scenarios
1st Scenario :-

1. Do want to run on Chrome or Edge ?
ChromeDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();

Mostly we will be using below 80% -
2. Do want to run on Chrome and then change to Edge?
WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
driver = new EdgeDriver();

3. Do want to run on multiple browsers ?
RemoteWebDriver driver (With GRID) - Advance (Last 2 Sessions)
